{# Shared network blocks for container compose templates.

   Every service template inlined the same two `networks:` blocks — the per-service
   attachment list and the top-level external declaration — looping over
   container_item.networks (falling back to the default docker_network). These two
   macros replace that boilerplate; they emit byte-identical output to the old inline
   loops, so a service can still append extra hardcoded networks on the lines that
   follow the macro call (e.g. karakeep's `- internal`, crowdsec's `crowdsec-db:`).

   `service_networks()` — the per-service `networks:` list. Invoke at the service's
   4-space indent so the key lands correctly:
       {{ service_networks() }}

   `external_networks()` — the top-level `networks:` stanza declaring each external.
   Invoke at column 0:
       {{ external_networks() }}

   Templates with bespoke per-service attachments (e.g. traefik) keep their networks
   inline — these macros are only for the standard loop.
#}
{% macro service_networks() -%}
networks:
{% for net in container_item.networks | default([docker_network]) %}
      - {{ net }}
{% endfor %}
{%- endmacro %}
{% macro external_networks() -%}
networks:
{% for net in container_item.networks | default([docker_network]) %}
  {{ net }}:
    external: true
{% endfor %}
{%- endmacro %}
